.\" Man page for card_mapper
.TH CARD_MAPPER 1 "2026-03-25" "LibreMiddleware" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
card_mapper \- smart card file system mapper and documentation generator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B card_mapper
.B \-\-discover
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B card_mapper
.B \-\-plugin
.I name
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B card_mapper
scans smart cards via PC/SC and generates Markdown documentation of their
file system structure, including ASCII tree diagrams, Mermaid diagrams,
and TLV data element tables.
.PP
It operates in two modes:
.B discover
mode for unknown cards (probing AIDs and FID ranges), and
.B plugin
mode for known card types (using protocol definitions from LibreMiddleware).
.PP
The generated documentation follows the applet/profile format used in
.IR LibreMiddleware/docs/cards/ .
.SH MODES
.TP
.B \-\-discover
Scan an unknown card: detect applets by probing known AIDs, walk the file
system by probing FID ranges (0x0F00\-0x0FFF, 0x0D00\-0x0DFF, 0xD000\-0xD0FF),
attempt TLV parsing on found files, and generate applet and profile documentation.
.TP
.BI \-\-plugin " name"
Map a known plugin's applet using its protocol definitions.
Supported plugins:
.BR eid ", " cardedge ", " health ", " vehicle ", " emrtd .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-output " file"
Write single applet doc to
.I file
(only valid with
.BR \-\-plugin ).
.TP
.BI \-\-output\-dir " dir"
Write applet and profile docs to
.IR dir .
Default:
.BR docs/cards/ .
Only valid with
.BR \-\-discover .
.TP
.BI \-\-scaffold " name"
Generate a draft
.I *_protocol.h
header for a new plugin from scan results.
Only valid with
.BR \-\-discover .
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Append an APDU trace section to the output, showing all command/response
pairs exchanged during the scan.
.TP
.BI \-\-reader " name"
Use a specific PC/SC reader. Default: first available reader.
.TP
.BI \-\-mrz " MRZ"
Authenticate via PACE using the given MRZ string (eMRTD cards).
.TP
.BI \-\-can " CAN"
Authenticate via PACE\-CAN using the given CAN (eMRTD cards).
.TP
.BI \-\-pin " ref"
Prompt for PIN interactively for the given PIN reference
(hex with 0x prefix or decimal). Used for PIN\-protected cards like CardEdge.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Scan an unknown card, write docs to default location:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-discover
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan unknown card with APDU trace, save to specific directory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-discover \-\-verbose \-\-output\-dir /tmp/card\-docs/
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan unknown card and scaffold a new plugin:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-discover \-\-scaffold mynewcard
.fi
.RE
.PP
Map Serbian eID applet from a card in the reader:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-plugin eid \-\-output docs/cards/applets/eid\-serbian\-applet.md
.fi
.RE
.PP
Map eMRTD applet with PACE-MRZ authentication:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-plugin emrtd \-\-mrz "P<SRBSMITH<<JOHN..." \-\-verbose
.fi
.RE
.PP
Map eMRTD applet with PACE\-CAN authentication:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-plugin emrtd \-\-can 123456
.fi
.RE
.PP
Map CardEdge applet with PIN (prompts interactively):
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-plugin cardedge \-\-pin 0x80
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use a specific reader when multiple are connected:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-discover \-\-reader "Alcor Micro AU9560"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Full workflow: discover card, scaffold plugin, with trace:
.PP
.RS
.nf
card_mapper \-\-discover \-\-scaffold neweid \-\-verbose \-\-output\-dir docs/cards/
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, card communication failure, etc.).
.TP
.B 2
No card present in reader.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pcscd (8),
.BR opensc\-tool (1)
.PP
.I docs/cards/
\(em generated card documentation
.PP
.I docs/CONTRIBUTING\-PLUGIN.md
\(em guide for adding new card plugins
